  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Thirty-seven consecutive patients who came to regular outpatient visits at our tertiary
        care institution were referred to CMR.

        Patient parameters were compared to a control group of 25 healthy age matched volunteers.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Eligibility criteria were an AS operation in childhood for correction of d-TGA and the
             absence of associated hemodynamically significant heart defects.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Exclusion criteria were usual CMR contraindications such as ferromagnetic metallic
             implants.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
